German Minister Schaeuble Rejects Joint Euro Region Bond Sales

-- B y   R a i n e r   B u e r g i n
-- 
2011-09-24T19:22:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-24/german-minister-schaeuble-rejects-joint-euro-region-bond-sales.html
German Finance Minister  Wolfgang
Schaeuble  said the euro region can’t sell government bonds
jointly because that would “destroy the system of sticks and
carrots” that forces governments to adhere to sustainable
fiscal policies. He was speaking at the  Institute of
International Finance  in  Washington .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rainer Buergin at 
 rbuergin1@bloomberg.net  